SIMPLE: sinistral
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sinistral
<hw>Sin"is*tral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to the left, inclining to the left; sinistrous; -- opposed to
<ant>dextral</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having the whorls of the spire
revolving or rising to the left; reversed; -- said of certain spiral
shells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinistrality</ent>⟦br⟧
